Totally agree here, [redacted].

We are the acquirer and the provider. To your point because we own the gateway and because of Lighthouse capabilities nobody can replace us. If somebody took the time and effort to replace us it would be a major project for them and one they have to price in.

The Card Connect acquisition helps us in two critical ways. First, it gives us a large base of ISV's and lets us do cross selling of the services to them. Second, and most important, it makes us the "problem solver" for very complex ISV's and Enterprise merchants. These merchants can look at us as the end all solution, as we now own the full stack.

I think we should focus on messaging around that.
